<br>
<br>
********** Chat Channels ********** <br>
<br>
Please use the following chat channels:<br>
<br>
FWRAID - raid wide chat<br>
FWLISTEN - important announcements only. This is where I talk, MA posts messages, snarers announce when snares land, etc. NO CHAT HERE.<br>
FWLEAD - all group leaders (first toon listed for each group) and raid leaders will communicate here. Please use chain of command whenever possible (toons -&gt; group leaders -&gt; raid leaders)<br>
<br>
********** Floorplan **************** <br>
<br>
Go to www.eqatlas.com and familiarize yourself with the layout Permafrost Keep. <br>
<br>
STAGING PHASE<br>
1. When you are in Everfrost report in to the raid leader.<br>
2. The raid leader may tell you if the raid is short of certain classes. Check with friends if asked.<br>
3. Turn off anonymous when you show up.<br>
4. The raid leader, pullers, and group Leaders will use FWLISTEN channel. All other communication should be on the FWRAID channel.<br>
5. It may take a while for the raid leader to work out final groups and the attack plan, especially if the raid is short of people in critical areas (clerics, enchanters, bards, and nukers).<br>
<br>
At all times do not move further forwards than your raid leader unless you are a designated puller.<br>
<br>
************ Resist Gear ************<br>
<br>
Try to acquire as much cold resist gear as possible, mages present will summon the appropriate +15 fire /cold resist all/all shoulder gear.<br>
<br>
Vox's most deadly weapon is her AE cold breath and AE fear spell. Wear as much MR/CR gear as possible; sacrifice all other statistics (yes, even AC) to get these as high as possible. If you are level 52, CR gear is more important that MR gear, because you will resist most of her fears if you have a bard in your group.<br>
<br>
If you don't have much, consider acquiring: 2xPlatinum Peridot Ring (AC4 CR10), Cloak of the Icebear (AC8 HP10 CR20), Rune Boned Fork (MR10 CR10 FR10), Crown of the Froglok King (AC12 CR20 FR20), Velium Round Shield (AC15 CR10), and Gnomish Environmental Suit (AC9 FR10 CR10 PR10). There are a wealth of other items available, especially with the addition of SoV.<br>
4. Many of the mobs in Permafrost have high cold resist - including Vox, use fire based spells where possible for minimum resists.<br>
<br>
Make sure both your resist equipment is easily accessible in one or two packs when you arrive.<br>
<br>
************ VOX ************<br>
<br>
[Excerpts from www.crimsontalon.com/raidvox.htm I recommend looking at this site in advance. ]<br>
<br>
We will zone into Permafrost Keep.<br>
<br>
Our path will be (using the eqatlas map for reference): [7] &quot;Flag Room&quot;, [3] &quot;King's Room&quot;, Pause to insure everyone is present, &amp; the puller will pull giants to the raid [2] Ice Giant Diplomat, to the hall at loc. approximately 900, 50. From here the raid will have the final giants pulled to it, and be buffed. It is imperative that you do not wander or move past the raid leader, or risk falling in one of a number of pit traps, if you should fall into a pit trap STAND AND DIE, do not train the raid, your corpse will be recovered at the end of the raid.<br>
<br>
Once again, at all times prior to charging the dragon do not move further forwards than your raid leader unless you are a designated puller.<br>
<br>
********** Buffing for Vox ********** <br>
<br>
Remember, buffing is the longest most boring part of raids. It is also the trickiest and most important. Please be patient, pay attention and execute your duties in this phase quickly - whether it is casting a single junk buff, singing a mana song or moving and camping at the right time. Things will get done much faster if we all do this.<br>
<br>
Buffing will be done in the hall at approximately 900, 0 while the raid waits at 900, 50.<br>
<br>
Buffing will done in groups. Each group will step up to the buffing area (at 900, 0) and get the following buffs, in order:<br>
<br>
#01 caster 1 junk buff (e.g. resist fire) <br>
#02 caster 1 junk buff (e.g. resist poison) <br>
#03 caster 1 junk buff (e.g. resist disease) <br>
<br>
Once you have all 3 Junk buffs please sit to indicate that you have them.<br>
<br>
#04 shaman stamina <br>
#05 shaman Harnessing of spirit <br>
#06 cleric shield of words <br>
#07 cleric Heroic Bond <br>
#08 cleric symbol of naltron (reagent: peridot)<br>
#09 enchanter rune IV / V (reagent: peridot)<br>
#10 enchanter group resist magic <br>
#11 druid circle of Summer<br>
#12 enchanter haste / clarity <br>
#13 open Chloro, Damage Shield, or open for Celestial Healing, etc.<br>
#14-15 open for bard resist songs <br>
<br>
Buffers will announce when they start and finish each buff ( buffers should make hotkeys). When the 'final' groups are posted a caster will be assigned to each buff, so check back before the raid.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Fully buffed groups will camp out to the FV chatroom immediately upon getting 11 buffs (12 for casters - clarity). Haste will be reapplied just before the charge. Relog every 20 minutes to refresh summoned items.<br>
<br>
Groups 1, and 2 will camp out at loc 925, - 10.<br>
All other groups will camp at 900, 50<br>
<br>
After all the melee groups and nuker groups have camped the buffers will med to full and buff themselves. When the buffers are back up to 80 mana from these final buffs everyone from the chatroom will be told to reenter the game.<br>
<br>
Remember to join FWLISTEN &amp; FWRAID channels when you return.<br>
<br>
********** Dragon Vox ********** <br>
<br>
General notes: <br>
1) Everyone should have hotkeys setup to announce significant actions. Group leaders should announce when their group has engaged, casters should announce attempts to debuff, etc.<br>
<br>
2) To land spells you need to be within Vox's melee/AoE range. Best place is right by his butt. This is why EVERYONE needs good resists, full buffs, etc.<br>
<br>
3) Healing. If we have dragon groups setup with no clerics in the melee groups, each group will have an assigned cleric (or two). When tanks need a heal they should 1) send a tell to their designated cleric (have a hotkey for this), 2) turn off attack and 3) back away from Vox &amp; towards their cleric once they no longer have aggro. Clerics should have hotkeys to target all of their designated tanks, as well as an /rtarget hotkey. If we get 3-4 clerics each tank group will have a cleric and this will be easier.<br>
<br>
4) Pushing. 20 tanks beating on Vox will push her around. It is imperative that Vox NOT get pushed into a wall. If Vox starts to get close to the lava MOVE YOUSELF so that you don't make it worse. MELEE BE PREPARED TO MOVE AROUND VOX AS A GROUP TO KEEP PUSHING HER AWAY FROM THE WALLS. You should always be between Vox and the nearest wall if in doubt. If necessary, melees should stop attacking and back away to get Vox back into the center of her room. Those that are between Vox and the nearest wall should not taunt. If you are near the wall and are the current agro, move away from the wall. Since Vox is a caster, it is best to have all melee on one side of Vox to push her as much as possible (now why the heck would we want to do that?), because it will interrupt her from casting Complete heal on herself, regardless of weather we manage to land any stuns or not. <br>
<br>
When all groups have reformed the MA group and SA group (groups 1 &amp; 2) will enter Vox’s chamber and engage. Tanks remember to activate disciplines. Bard's priorties are 1) Elemental Rhythms, 2) Guardian Rhythms - have your best drum out. Haven't figured out what would be the best 3rd song to twist (if possible), but it needs to be low aggro. Also, bards should NOT be attacking Vox. 1) puts you up the aggro list, 2) minimal damage output when you have a drum going, 3) Ripostes will kill you quick. We need the bards alive to keep our resists up.<br>
<br>
As soon as the MA group has engaged Vox and has her positioned in the middle of her lair all remaining melee groups will enter and position themselves behind Vox. MAKE SURE YOU ARE NOT PUSHING VOX TOWARDS A NEARBY WALL. The casters can move up from the hall to the entrance of [1] Vox’s chanber (I will have a hotkey to announce such).<br>
<br>
Healing the MT will start with paladin LoH rotation, and then the clerics will take over. It is imperative that paladins and clerics announce heals in FWGLISTEN. Furthermore, Paladins now get DA at 51 - use it when Vox beats on you after your LoH, BUT ANNOUNCE IT SO THE CLERICS DON'T WASTE TIME TRYING TO HEAL YOU.<br>
<br>
If for any reason, you get feared and find yourself in the pits, stay there and die. Do not bring more mobs to the fight.<br>
<br>
Every enchanter should run to Vox and dispel two times to remove all her buffs (remember to stand within melee range). If short on enc, other classes can dispell. Vox has the old-world max of 32k hitpoints, and the dispels should remove her cleric buffs and will effectively reduce her hitpoints. Each enchanter should OOC &quot;Dispelled&quot; once two successful dispells are complete. Need a minimum of 3 dispellers.<br>
Once finished dispelling, enchanters should immediately begin mana sieving her, and continue to sieve until Vox is dead. If short on enchanters (1-2), suggest having any necros feed mana. Necros can also DoT and send in pet.<br>
<br>
Healers should remain near the rock until needed. If there is only a single person in the group taking damage, they should move back to the rock and get a heal. This allows the healers to stay out of Vox's breath range. If a number of people have taken damage, the healer should come to the group. The safest place for a healer to stand is behind Vox outside breath range.<br>
<br>
Necros DO NOT use spells that turn Vox into a skeleton. This makes it very difficult to find the mob with so many people.<br>
<br>
Healers should pay particularly close attention to the bard in their group. Bard resistances are preventing an enormous amount of damage, and bards have the fewest HP of all melee/hybrids. Bards are the only class that will not come back to the rock for healing if they are the only one taking damage. Bards are keeping groups alive, keep them alive.<br>
<br>
<br>
At 60-70 Health:<br>
Pets are called in to attack. <br>
An enchanter can attempt tash. If Vox agros and stays agroed on the enchanter, they should not be healed (hate will be transferred to healer and healer will die). Heal the enchanter if they live. If agroed, the enchanter can use this opportunity to pull Vox into the center of the room. The risk to enc tashing is rather low by the time Vox has reached the 60 percent mark. <br>
Once all dispells are done, the debufs should come. Shamans should immediately begin to attempt to slow/debuf Vox and should OOC successes (&quot;Slowed&quot;, &quot;Malosied&quot;, etc). <br>
Bards may consider adding a debuf to twist (1 does fire resist, 1 does magic resist). If any 53+ characters are present on the raid, they can attempt to attack/debuf/slow at this time. (or DOT/nuke/group heal, whatever one spell you can add before you get booted).<br>
Everyone begins chain-stunning, bashing, and slamming Vox. Although, stuns will not actually stun her, it will interrupt her from casting heal spells. Continue to stun her until she is dead. Vox is a cleric AI and will attempt to Complete Heal herself. If she does get one off, it is not the end of the world, it will heal approximately 5k of hitpoints.<br>
<br>
At 50 Health:<br>
Nukers (other than Wizzys) charge, get under and behind Vox and blast away, when out of mana, get out of AoE / melee range. Remember to get within melee range or your spell will not land. Melee classes that cannot cast stun should nuke as well. Nuke until Vox is dead. Cold based spells may have a reduced effect (correct me if I'm wrong).<br>
If a bard is nearly dead and cannot be healed, they can suicide with Denons Desperate Dirge (Vox targeted) for 300+ damage.<br>
<br>
At 20 Health:<br>
Wizards are called in at 20% health for nuking, get under and behind Vox and blast away.<br>
Continue to mana sieve, interrupt, and nuke Vox until dead.<br>
<br>
Hopefully enough of us live to take her down.<br>
<br>
