<br>
The only outright problem I observed was that there wasn't enough time to haste the melees before we engaged. All I had on me was Capt Nalot. This obviously, with our melee-heavy force, severely hurt our overall damage output. I think if we'd all had even alacrity on, it might have made the difference. The reasoning for charging without it was that in the time it would have taken to haste everyone, other buffs would have started fading.<br>
<br>
This raised a question in my mind, and I'm not bitching, I'm just asking for anyone else's opinion on this because I really don't understand the policy. Findra does this on all of her raids too: all the buffs are applied group by group, with the groups camping to desktop once they're fully buffed, to preserve the buff timers. Makes sense. Except for haste. Haste, for some reason, is held for last and then applied all at once on everyone after they return from chat. I never understood this. It completely drains the haster, not to mention the entire raid has to stand there waiting (with buff timers ticking) while everyone has haste cast on them. Wouldn't it make more sense to apply haste at the end of the normal group-by-group buff cycle, and have people camp out to preserve it just like all their other buffs?<br>
<br>
The only reasoning for doing it all at the end that made any kind of sense to me was the notion that buffs tend not to get applied in the listed order anyway, so haste gets saved for last to make sure it's at the bottom of the buff list. And that seems pretty weak to me. Haste should be toward the bottom, yes. I'd rather scream at the haster to frigging wait till I had the rest of my buffs before casting it, than stand around twitching and worrying that my buffs would fade before he got around to hasting everyone at once.<br>
<br>
If anyone can offer some insight that I'm missing, I'd love to hear it. Findra maybe? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umykelanjelo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mykelanjelo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Teenage Mutant Ninja Looter</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/25/02 4:53:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teusday Night OPEN VOX Raid - Teus 9/24 9:00pm EST </span><hr size=1> I just wanna shout out to everyone that attended....You guys were great.  In a way, I feel we were successful, even without slaying Vox. Everyone seemed to be having fun, something this server lacks alot of.  The pulling was straight up AMAZING (i don't mean to toot my own horn), as Kenea, Rafeal, and myself pulled off some stuff that we honestly didnt think we could do (like falling down pits that we blatantly KNEW were there).  I REALLY want another crack at her, and would prefer that all of you that were there come along, as well as some new faces.  Anyway, its 6am here, so i better get to bed...once again, a big pat on the back to EVERYONE that was involved. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316668" border=0>Inspect Me</a><br><a href="http://www.screamparks.net/hosted/nightmare"><img src="http://www.screamparks.net/hosted/nightmare/images/tulipsig.jpeg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showPrevMessage?topicID=116.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboa